{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Regulate companies supplying heating oil and LPG",
        "additional_details": "As an example, the price of heating oil doubled in the first couple of weeks of March for oil which had already reached the UK side of the supply lines before the start of the war with Iran.\r\n\r\nCurrently suppliers are operating outside of any government regulation.\r\nThe industry should be regulated, and when necessary price capped by the government.",
        "background": "We are concerned that liquefied petroleum gas suppliers of heating oil and liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) are profiteering during geo-political crisis, and when any potential disruption to supply is reported by the media.",
